On a final note, animal rights activists can be real knuckleheads. There was an animal rights rally in my home town, held in the vicinity of a couple grade schools. They were trying to impress on youngsters that drinking milk was a violation of cows and stole nutrience from calves.  Can you imagine the negative impact they had on more than a handful of impressionable minds that day? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uizdaari.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Izdaari</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=#FFFF66>Board Moderator<br><font color=#A0B0E0>&lt;Evoluxa&gt; </font></span><br>  Posts: 457<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/1/01 9:58:48 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.cyberlink.bc.ca/~evoluxa/roster/boardpics/izdaari_small.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: McDonald's lawsuit..</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the link, Thomus! I often cook up some GardenBurgers at home, and it's good to know of more such products. I see Denny's serves Boca burgers, so I'll try one next time I eat there. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
And once again, I have no problem with eating meat and I like it as much as any of you carnivores, but I think the typical American diet (especially the fast food version) includes way too much meat and not nearly enough veggies and fruits for a healthy balance.<br>
